{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EJ4YsMHzxhTmihxyQCp9YM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The bug is now crystal clear. Here's my diagnosis:\n\n---\n\n**ROOT CAUSE:** `libyara/scan.c:199` — The function `_yr_scan_wicompare` compares wide (UTF-16 LE) data against an ASCII pattern using case-insensitive comparison. In UTF-16 LE, every ASCII character is encoded as two bytes: the ASCII value followed by a `0x00` high byte. The buggy commit removed the essential check `*(s1 + 1) == 0x00`, which verified that the high byte of each wide character is null. Without this check, characters like `0x20 0xF7` (UTF-16 U+F720) are falsely treated as equal to ASCII space `0x20`, because the low-byte comparison `yr_lowercase[0x20] == yr_lowercase[0x20]` succeeds while ignoring the high byte `0xF7`. This allows the rule `\" cmd.exe \" nocase wide` to incorrectly match a blob containing `0x20 0xF7 0x63 0x00...` instead of `0x20 0x00 0x63 0x00...`.\n\n**LOCAL FIX:** Restore the removed high-byte check in the while-loop condition at `scan.c:199`:\n\n```c\nwhile (i < string_length &&\n       yr_lowercase[*s1] == yr_lowercase[*s2] &&\n       *(s1 + 1) == 0x00)\n```\n\n**GLOBAL FIX:** The structural fix is to make `_yr_scan_wicompare` explicitly validate the UTF-16 encoding invariant as a precondition: the loop should advance `s1` by 2 bytes per character (as it already does), but it must assert or check that the high byte `*(s1 + 1)` is `0x00` before considering the character as a match candidate. More broadly, any function that \"widens\" an ASCII pattern for wide-string comparison should enforce that matched code units fall strictly within the Basic Latin block (U+0000–U+007F), i.e., high byte must be zero. This invariant can be centralized into a helper (e.g., `is_wide_ascii_char(s1)`) used consistently across all wide-comparison paths in the scanner, preventing a whole class of false-positive matches where non-ASCII UTF-16 characters are conflated with their ASCII low-byte counterparts."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":768,"cache_read_input_tokens":27506,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":768},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cde5cbb7-707e-4acd-929c-7a7d51ae0929","uuid":"542f9768-1525-49cf-b4fc-4ccdbe0978cc"}
